Transform>> Statistics>>Analysis>>Dashboard


Change data set to a table

Ctrl+T

01. To trim odd spaces in a column

--> =TRIM([@Column Name])
     =TRIM([@Manager])


02. TO select  a column 
--> Ctrl +Shift+down arrow


03. To Copy: Ctrl + C
    To Paste: Alt + H + VV 

04. To Remove column 
    Select Column>> Ctrl -

05. To Round up number in column with decimals
    =ROUNDUP([@Quantity],num_digit)
    =ROUNDUP([@Quantity],0)

06. To add country or religion for the city column
    Data>> Geography
    Add column symbol appears>>Country/Region

07. Remove Duplicates
    Data>>Remove Duplicates>>ok

08. To turn on data analysis option in Excel
    File>> Option>> add in>> Analysis Toolpak>> Go>>  
    Analysis Toolpak>>ok
    Appears on right top screen 
    Data Analysis>> Descriptive Statistics>> OK
    
    Input Range>> Select Column with nos(Ctrl+Shift+down 
    key)>>  Summary Statistics on>>Output Range ON>>up arrow>> Select a cell where you want statistics

We get mean medain mode minimum max sum count


Inser>> Statistics Chart>>  
